pulation will influence the nation's political future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCities and townszUnited States. 0aCommunitieszUnited States. 0aRural populationzUnited StatesxAttitudes. 0aSociology, RuralzUnited States. 0aWorking class whiteszUnited StatesxAttitudes. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Rural.2bisacsh1 aWuthnow, Robert, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691195155zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691195155423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691195155/original  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles